This paper deals with the efficient delivery of multicast video services over 4G networks, which involves aspects of network infrastructure, multimedia processing, information theory, cryptography, and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which covers topics related to the design, analysis, and optimization of communication networks. Other likely sub-categories include cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which are relevant to the multimedia processing, error correction, security, and distributed optimization aspects of the proposed framework.
